Sentencas: LaCrO3 doped with calcium and cerium on the A-site in the series of La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-delta (LCCC3060, LCCC4050, LCCC5040, LCCC6030 corresponding to x = 0.6, 0.5, 0.4, and 0.3 respectively), is synthesized by a sol gel combustion method and evaluated as anode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-δ as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Relatively higher Ca-doping on La in LaCrO3 is found to improve both electronic and ionic conductivity.
Titulo: La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-δ as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LCCC compositions have demonstrated good chemical stability in reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-δ as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Evaluation of the LCCC material as anode in symmetrical cell configuration shows that the highest Ca-doping composition results in the lowest activation energy and the lowest polarization resistance.
Titulo: La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-δ as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte-supported single cells with LCCC3060 as the anode and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) as the cathode show that LCCC3060 can be a potential anode material for H-2, but not for CH4.
Titulo: La0.9-xCaxCe0.1CrO3-δ as potential anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
